TRAINING and TESTING THE MODELS¶

Training and testing dataset using the Supevised Machine Learning algorithms are used to train the model. The training set has 80% from the dataset and prediction is done using the remaining 20% data

#Reference : https://towardsdev.com/outlier-detection-using-iqr-method-and-box-plot-in-python-82e1e15232bd
#Code snippet to check the outliers in the "BMI" feature 

def find_outliers_IQR(df):
    q3=df.quantile(0.75)
    q1=df.quantile(0.25)    
    IQR=q3-q1
    outliers_ = df[((df<(q1-1.5*IQR)) | (df>(q3+1.5*IQR)))]
    return outliers_


outliers = find_outliers_IQR(df_new['BMI'])
print(outliers)
print("BMI Outliers: ", str(len(outliers)))
print("max BMI outlier value: ", str(outliers.max()))
print("min BMI outlier value:  ", str(outliers.min()))
